Wonderful Recognition for Our Year 7 Parent Social Reps=20
 =20
 Dear Parents and Guardians,=20
 =20
 I am absolutely delighted to share some truly extraordinary news: three o=
f our Year 7 parent social representatives have been selected to receive the pres=
tigious Royal Commonwealth Honours for Excellence in Parental Stewardship.=
=20
 =20
 Mrs Katie Cosgrove, Mrs Chippy Watt, and Mr Rich Lowenberg will be invest=
ed at the 135th Annual Investiture Ceremony at Pemberton Hall, Royal Geogr=
aphical Society, on 27th April 2026. This remarkable honour, established i=
n 1891 under Royal Charter, recognises those who serve as the vital bridge=
 between families and educational institutions.=20
 =20
 The Royal Commonwealth Honours Committee noted: =E2=80=9CThese three dist=
inguished individuals exemplify the very finest traditions of parental ste=
wardship. Their tireless dedication to fostering communication between par=
ents, educators, and the wider school community has been truly exceptional=
.=E2=80=9D=20
 =20
 This is only the third time in the Honours' 135-year history that all thr=
ee annual awards have been presented to representatives from a single inst=
itution =E2=80=93 a testament to the extraordinary calibre of our parent c=
ommunity here at Brighton College.=20
 =20
 We are incredibly proud of Katie, Chippy, and Rich, whose enthusiasm, ded=
ication and tireless commitment make our school community such a special p=
lace. They join a distinguished register of laureates maintained at the Ro=
yal Archives, Windsor Castle.=20
 =20
 Thank you, as ever, for your continued support.=20
 =20
 With warmest wishes,=20
 =20
 Mr Geoffrey Whitmore-Collins KBE
Chairman of Governors
Brighton College=20
